<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-058-227 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 292 261</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 16 1991 v25 n37 p93(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Getting acquainted, high-tech style: databases of consumer buyinghabits are gaining momentum with food marketers. (includes relatedarticle on card-based preferred shopper programs)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Horwitt, Elisabeth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Food marketers are taking advantage of advanced database targetingto gather data about buying habits of consumers.andP;  Databases arebecoming increasingly important because households are fragmented.andO;Marketers can take the data and pinpoint consumer groups and morespecific consumer marketing means better use of promotionaldollars.andP;  Database targeting also enables marketers to createpersonalized mailings to establish long-term relationships withcustomers.andP;  The critical ingredient for success is obtainingconsumers' addresses and telephone numbers.andP;  Manufacturers gatherthis data by offering rebates or creating toll-free numberservices to address complaints and for sending free recipes andcoupons.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Marketing StrategyPromotion of ProductMarketing ResearchFood industryData basesConsumer behavior.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>